Reasoning: The paper discusses algorithms and data structures for listing all maximal independent sets and maintaining dynamic dominance in sparse graphs. This falls under the category of graph algorithms and data structures, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as it covers the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as it covers combinatorial structures and graph theory. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as it covers algorithms and data structures for geometric problems, which can be applied to graph problems. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely but still possible categories as they cover algorithms and data structures for distributed and parallel computing and the complexity of algorithms, respectively.
